eir partners. The book details applied theories of aggression in conjunction with the skills required for dealing with anger, conflict and aggression. A set of tools and reflective exercises assists the application of theory to day-to-day child protection practice. This indispensable and practical text is ideal for social work students, practitioners, trainers and academics specialising in child protection.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAggressiveness. 0aChild welfarexServices forzGreat Britain. 0aChild welfarexServices forzScotland. 0aSocial work with childrenzGreat Britain. 0aSocial work with childrenzScotland. 0aViolencezGreat BritainxPrevention. 0aViolencezScotlandxPrevention. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978184742922340uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447314141?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447314141423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447314141/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013